Opening Spaces for healthy, secure and meaningful Relationships ‚Äî with yourself and others.
Understanding how to work through our triggers. When we are ‚Äútriggered‚Äù it is usually because something in the present moment reminds us of a past event. This can cause us to react in a way that is disproportionate to the current situation because we are actually reacting to the unresolved emotions and event from the past. In this sense, triggers are like emotional time capsules that hold memories, thoughts, and feelings from the past. By understanding the root cause of our triggers and the past events that are associated with them, we can work towards healing and resolving the emotions that are still affecting us in the present.
It is important to recognize when we are triggered and take steps to ground ourselves so that we can respond in a more mature and balanced way.
